==English==

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|acid|fy}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|acidus||sour, acid|lang=la}}; compare French {{term|acidifier|lang=fr}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|En-us-acidify.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|acidif|i|ed}}

# to make something (more) [[acidic]] or [[sour]]; to convert into an [[acid]].
# to [[neutralize]] [[alkalis]], as to '''acidify''' sugar
# to sour, to [[embitter]].
#:* His thin existence all '''acidified''' into rage. - [[w:Thomas Carlyle|Thomas Carlyle]]

